summary: Highly motivated and passionate law graduate with a strong academic background in Human Rights and Migration. Thorough knowledge of the legal framework for EU migration and asylum policy as well as of international human rights instruments. Advanced ability to analyze information and work on legal cases with little or no supervision. Detail-oriented, creative and hard-working. Time-flexible, adaptable in new working environments and driven by strong work ethics.
